border-radius: 15px;">
Register

About AISOC

AISOC was launched in 2024 to fill the growing gap in AI education and democratize access to world-class AI skills. With the rise and prominence of large foundation models and generative AI, and how these technologies are reshaping the world of software, it is now more important than ever to raise talents that are equipped to build the next generation of AI systems and GenAI-powered applications. And we are taking on this mission!

Through intense, hands-on technical training in the foundations, engineering and applications of modern AI systems, AISOC stars develop rigorous understanding and mastery of the technical skills needed to build next-gen intelligent applications and push the boundaries of the AI landscape.

Learn how to build LLM chatbots, RAG-powered applications, and agentic systems for real-world use cases. You will design APIs that interact with frontier models and external tools to provide retrieval, reasoning and conversational capabilities. Become a confident AI application developer using powerful AI tools and technologies.



See More
TRACK II: MACHINE LEARNING

LEVEL - BEGINNER / INTERMEDIATE


Learn the "craftsmanship" of machine learning, including principles and practical techniques of preparing data, designing training experiments, calibrating models, and choosing the right metrics for evaluation. Master the underlying algorithms for a wide range of ML tasks, and ML engineering techniques for building production-ready models.



See More

LEVEL - INTERMEDIATE

You will pretrain and finetune large models on GPUs, serve them on compute infra, and optimize them using distributed inference and autoscaling techniques.



See More
TRACK IV: PRODUCTION AI

LEVEL - INTERMEDIATE


Become a specialist in the deployment and management of AI applications at scale. You will learn how to take AI models, RAG applications and agentic systems into production. Master the engineering best practices for designing, deploying and running scalable AI systems that serve real users in production.



See More

    Beginners to LLMs and generative AI systems who want to gain mastery in the development of LLM-powered applications, chatbots, RAG pipelines and agentic systems. Target audience includes, but is not limited to, software developers, data professionals, researchers, ML engineers, technical product managers, etc, at any levels.


MACHINE LEARNING

    Data analysts/scientists, researchers, developers, or beginners seeking to understand what it takes to build high-performing machine learning models that generalize well in the reeal world. ML engineering focus targetted at practicing data scientists and ML engineers seeking to master the engineering of scalable ML systems.

AI engineers, researchers, or data scientists seeking to understand the underlying principles of building and serving large language models. Suitable for folks with some ML background or prior experience prototyping LLM applications such as RAG, QA systems and agents. Mathematically inclined folks with computational experience are also welcome to apply.


PRODUCTION AI

    Software developers or ML/AI/data engineers seeking to build production-grade AI systems or integrate LLMs into software applications or production data/ML pipelines. Prior experience building traditional software, data pipelines or traditional ML systems is a plus. Familiarity prototyping LLM applications or working with OSS models and LLM APIs is also a plus.

Akolade Hamzat

AI/ML ENGINEER

The experience from AISOC directly contributed to landing my first full-time international role as a Senior ML/AI Engineer. I joined AISOC at a time when I was seriously considering leaving Data Science for Mobile Development, but everything changed during the program. The depth of expertise from the speakers and clarity with which they taught reignited my passion for Al and helped me rediscover my path.

I connected deeply with a few members of the faculty and maintained those relationships beyond the program. With the guidance of David Okpare, I built my first Agentic Al system, and ever since I have grown more confident in managing end-to-end AI projects. I also aced several interviews and landed my current role shortly after. AISOC didn't just sharpen my skills. It clarified my direction and unlocked real opportunities. I'm grateful to the AISOC team for creating a program that truly delivers.
